---
const marginMeans = [
  { number: '01', label: 'Job loss', detail: 'You can weather the storm without losing your home.' },
  { number: '02', label: 'Medical bills', detail: 'The unexpected doesn\'t have to become catastrophic.' },
  { number: '03', label: 'Opportunity', detail: 'You can say yes when the right moment appears.' },
  { number: '04', label: 'Breathing', detail: 'You stop living paycheck to paycheck in your mind.' },
];
---

<section class="py-24 md:py-36 bg-warm-cream">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-storehouse-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase reveal">
        The lesson
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-text-deep leading-[1.05] reveal reveal-delay-1">
        Margin beats maximization.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <!-- Core insight -->
    <div class="mt-12 max-w-2xl reveal reveal-delay-2">
      <p class="text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed">
        Bob understood something most people miss:
        <span class="font-semibold text-text-deep">The goal isn't to get
        the most. It's to have enough &mdash; with room to spare.</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Margin provides: editorial numbered list -->
    <div class="mt-16 grid gap-0 divide-y divide-text-faint/20">
      {marginMeans.map((item) => (
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 md:gap-8 py-8 first:pt-0 last:pb-0 reveal">
          <div class="md:col-span-1">
            <span class="font-display text-xl text-storehouse-500/60">
              {item.number}
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-3 mt-1 md:mt-0">
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-text-deep">
              {item.label}
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-8 mt-2 md:mt-0">
            <p class="text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              {item.detail}
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Pull quote transition -->
    <div class="mt-20 flex justify-center reveal">
      <div class="w-16 h-px bg-text-faint/30"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center reveal">
      <p class="font-quote text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-text-deep italic leading-snug">
        "That lesson shaped everything since &mdash; twenty years in real estate,
        teaching buyers to leave margin. Then building The Candid Agent.
        And now, Storehouse."
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6 font-display text-xl text-storehouse-600">
        It's the Bob principle, applied to every dollar.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
